title: Cyclist could smell decomposed body of Karen Ristevski | Daily Mail Online
text: Man who lives next to the 'eerie' bushland where decomposing body of Karen Ristevski was found reveals he noticed 'an awful smell' in the area in weeks before she was discovered Man noticed a bad smell 50 metres from the hidden body of Karen Ristevski Ian Flannery, 61, thought he smelled 'a rotting kangaroo' when cycled by the area He has lived in the 'generally deserted' Salisbury Road area for eight years Mr Flannery say he doesn't recall seeing anyone in a van or looking suspicious Bushwalker found her 'badly decomposed' body under a large log on Monday Ms Ristevski disappeared after leaving her home on June 29 last year Published: 23:36 GMT, 24 February 2017 | Updated: 04:09 GMT, 25 February 2017 71 shares
